{{document-title title="Reports"}}
{{page-header title="Reports"}}

{{#page-body}}
  {{#if (can 'read about')}}
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-offset-2 col-md-4">
        <h2>Reading span</h2>
        <p>Your reading-span can have a significant impact on what you interpret in a sentence. Here's where you stand compared to the other participants.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
        {{profile-chart values=readingSpans profileValue=profileReadingSpan xtitle="Reading span (number of words)"}}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-offset-2 col-md-4">
        <h2>Writing time</h2>
        <p>Some people write fast but make more mistakes &mdash; others take more time and pay more attention. Where do you stand?</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
        {{profile-chart values=writingTimes profileValue=profileWritingTime xtitle="Writing time (% of allotted time)"}}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-offset-2 col-md-4">
        <h2>Transformation rate</h2>
        <p>Every one of us makes sense of a sentence differently, depending on our own experience and what we expect.</p>
        <p>A coarse measure of how much we transform is to look at the average number of characters we change when we rewrite a sentence (brought back to the original sentence length).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4">
        {{profile-chart values=errs profileValue=profileErr xtitle="Transformation rate"}}
      </div>
    </div>
  {{else}}
    <h2>Want to know what this is about?</h2>
    <h2><a href="#" {{action 'passExperiment'}}>Pass the experiment</a> first!</h2>
    <p>You can even <a href={{prolificStudyUrl}}>get paid for it</a>!</p>
  {{/if}}{{! can read about }}
{{/page-body}}
